==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: phagocyte
<hw>phag"o*cyte</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧g"⟦osl⟧*s⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>fagei^n</grk> to eat + <grk>ky`tos</grk> a hollow
vessel.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A leucocyte which plays a part
in immunity and retrogressive processes by taking up (eating), in the
form of fine granules, foreign objects such as bacteria or cellular
parts to be removed. There are two principle subtypes, (1)
<stype>microphages</stype>, polymorphonuclear lymphocytes which
principally digest bacteria; and (2) <stype>macrophages</stype>,
mononucleated cells which primarily scavenge dead tissue and degenerate
cells.</def> <rj><au>Stedman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phainopepla</ent>⟦br⟧
